ine might be usefully informed by sociology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCriminology. 0aWar and crime. 0aWar crimes. 0abicssc / Human rights. 0abicssc / War crimes. 0abisacsh / POLITICAL SCIENCE / Genocide et War Crimes. 0abisacsh / POLITICAL SCIENCE / Human Rights. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh1 aMillie, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWalklate, Sandra, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z97831111966880 cprintz978152920266340uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781529202618?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529202618423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529202618/original  a978-3-11-119668-8  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles